Test: is.positive.definite

Ivan Jacob Agaloos Pesigan

2020-07-16

Source: vignettes/tests/test_is.positive.definite.Rmd
test_is.positive.definite.Rmd
library(testthat)
library(jeksterslabRmatrix)
context("Test is.positive.definite.")

Parameters

F <- matrix(
  data = c(1, 2, 2, 1),
  ncol = 2
)
T <- diag(2)
knitr::kable(
  x = F,
  row.names = FALSE,
  caption = "Non-Positive Definite Matrix"
)
#> Warning in kable_pipe(x = structure(c("1", "2", "2", "1"), .Dim = c(2L, : The
#> table should have a header (column names)
Non-Positive Definite Matrix
1 2
2 1 
knitr::kable(
  x = T,
  row.names = FALSE,
  caption = "Positive Definite Matrix"
)
#> Warning in kable_pipe(x = structure(c("1", "0", "0", "1"), .Dim = c(2L, : The
#> table should have a header (column names)
Positive Definite Matrix
1 0
0 1

Results

knitr::kable(
  x = data.frame(
    Item = c(
      "Non-Positive Definite Matrix",
      "Positive Definite Matrix"
    ),
    Parameter = c(
      "FALSE",
      "TRUE"
    ),
    Results = c(
      is.positive.definite(F),
      is.positive.definite(T)
    )
  ),
  row.names = FALSE
)
Item Parameter Results
Non-Positive Definite Matrix FALSE FALSE
Positive Definite Matrix TRUE TRUE

testthat

test_that("is.positive.definite is TRUE", {
  expect_true(
    is.positive.definite(T)
  )
})
test_that("is.positive.definite is FALSE", {
  expect_false(
    is.positive.definite(F)
  )
})
test_that("is.positive.definite is FALSE (expect_error)", {
  expect_error(
    is.positive.definite(F, stop = TRUE)
  )
})
